episodes.title: The Cat and the Canary
episodes.plot: Black Canary convinces Green Arrow to help save her mentor, Wildcat, from his involvement in an underground, super-powered fight club known as MetaBrawl.

episodes.title: The Ties That Bind
episodes.plot: Mister Miracle and Big Barda solicit Justice League assistance to free Oberon from Apokolips. J'onn refuses, but Flash decides to help out on his own.

episodes.title: The Doomsday Sanction
episodes.plot: Superman battles Doomsday in the heart of a volcano. Doomsday is revealed to be a modified clone of Superman. Batman probes the Cadmus conspiracy to destroy the Justice League.

episodes.title: Task Force X
episodes.plot: Cadmus has recruited a team of supervillains named Task Force X (based on the comics' Suicide Squad) made up of Deadshot, Plastique, Captain Boomerang, and the Clock King. Their mission: steal the Annihilator armor from the Watchtower.

episodes.title: The Balance
episodes.plot: To help her magic superhero friends, the God Hermes sends Wonder Woman on a mission to help free Hades from the clutches of Felix Faust.

episodes.title: Double Date
episodes.plot: Seeking to avenge the death of her parents, the Huntress enlists the help of the Question in tracking down Steven Mandragora, a mobster in protective custody -- and being guarded by the Green Arrow and Black Canary.

episodes.title: Clash
episodes.plot: Captain Marvel joins the Justice League and his innocent presence inadvertently causes friction with Superman.

episodes.title: Hunter's Moon
episodes.plot: Shayera, Vixen and Vigilante are lured into an ambush by Thanagarians seeking revenge.

episodes.title: Question Authority
episodes.plot: The Question, fearing disaster, decides to kill Lex Luthor to avert it.

episodes.title: Flashpoint
episodes.plot: Lex Luthor executes his masterstroke to eliminate Project Cadmus and frame the Justice League.

episodes.title: Panic in the Sky
episodes.plot: While the senior Leaguers struggle to respond to the mysterious main gun firing, Amanda Waller orders Galatea to lead a full attack on the Justice League.

episodes.title: Divided We Fall
episodes.plot: The Justice League charter members must battle the combined Lex Luthor/Brainiac menace alone.

episodes.title: Epilogue
episodes.plot: In the future, Terry McGinnis learns the truth about his birth.
